# =============================================================================
# .gitignore for Terraform
# =============================================================================

# --- STATE FILES: NEVER COMMIT THESE ---
# State files contain PLAINTEXT SECRETS: passwords, private keys, tokens.
# They live in S3 instead. A local copy in git is a security incident.
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*
*.tfstate.backup

# --- Provider plugins (hundreds of MB, re-downloaded by terraform init) ---
.terraform/
.terraform.lock.hcl.bak

# --- Crash logs (may contain sensitive values) ---
crash.log
crash.*.log

# --- Variable files that may hold secrets ---
# NOTE: terraform.tfvars IS committed in this project on purpose. It holds
# only your IP address, no secrets. But these variants often hold secrets:
*.auto.tfvars
*secret*.tfvars
*private*.tfvars
secrets.tfvars

# --- Saved plan files (contain full resource values, including secrets) ---
*.tfplan
tfplan
plan.out

# --- Realm files with real credentials ---
# The .example file is safe. Exported realms may contain user data or
# client secrets, so exclude real ones by default.
realms/*-realm.json
!realms/*.example

# --- Certificates and keys ---
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
*.crt

# --- OS and editor noise ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*~
